      <p><a href="ch73s10.html#MonstersAnimals32">Camels</a> are known for their ability to travel long distances without food or water.</p>
      <p>The statistics presented here are for the dromedary, or one-humped <a href="ch73s10.html#MonstersAnimals32">camel</a>, which thrives in warm deserts. A dromedary stands about 7 feet tall at the shoulder, with its hump rising 1 foot higher. The two-humped, or Bactrian, <a href="ch73s10.html#MonstersAnimals32">camel</a> is suited to cooler, rocky areas. It is stockier, slower (speed 40 feet), and has a higher Constitution score (16).</p>
